header.gameNote: SAN JUAN SHOOTOUT AT SAN JUAN PR

article.headline: Appalachian State 75, UCF 64
article.story: GUAYNABO, Puerto Rico (AP) -- Nathan Cranford scored 18 points to lead Appalachian State to a 75-64 win over UCF in the semifinals of the San Juan Shootout on Wednesday at Morales Coliseum. Appalachian State (9-3) shot 50.9 percent for the game and 48 percent from 3-point range. The team led 37-30 at halftime, and UCF (7-2) couldn't catch up. Along with Cranford's 18 points, Donte Minter scored 13 points for Appalachian State. Another 10 points came from Jeremy Clayton, who also grabbed 10 rebounds. UCF's Jermaine Taylor made 16 points, Lavell Payne totaled 13 points and Mike O'Donnell added another 10 points. Appalachian State will play Vanderbilt for the tournament championship, and UCF will face Tennessee Tech in the tournament's third-place game.
